# The replay viewer bundle is generated by `pnpm -F viewer build` (Vite) and
# committed so pip installs ship it without a Node toolchain. Mark it generated
# so it collapses in PR diffs and doesn't skew language stats. Kept at repo
# root (not inside viewer_dist/) because Vite's emptyOutDir wipes that dir on
# every rebuild.
#
# Pin LF: the bundle is built on CI (Linux → LF) and the `js` job asserts the
# checked-in copy matches a fresh build. Without this, a Windows checkout
# (core.autocrlf=true) commits CRLF and the freshness check fails on line
# endings alone.
sdk-python/src/vibewarz/viewer_dist/** linguist-generated=true text eol=lf
